x4freetext: Experiment was performed at the
Edwards accelerator laboratory of Ohio University
using the 4.5-MV tandem Van de Graaff accelerator
Outgoing neutrons were registered using three
NE213 neutron detectors, which were positioned inside
an underground tunnel to reduce background radiation.
Neutron energies were obtained by the time-of-flight
technique with a flight path of 6.93 m.
Neutron energies were obtained by the time-
of-flight technique with a flight path of 6.93 m.
Pulse shape discrimination was utilized to identify
the neutrons. The neutron emission spectra were
measured at angles of 20, 40, 60, 80, 100, 120, 130,
140, and 150deg using a beam swinger facility.
